    "date": "1979-05-01",
    "source": {
      "work": "From Triangles to Manifolds",
      "chapter": null
    },
    "content": {
      "html": "<p>Let the surface \\(\\Sigma\\) be smooth and oriented. At every point \\(p \\in \\Sigma\\) there is a unit normal vector \\(v(p)\\) which is perpendicular to the tangent plane to \\(\\Sigma\\) at \\(p\\).</p>"
    },
